      "message": "the file permission errors you\u0027re talking about are when the openssh client refuses to use a private key (or sshd refuses to honor authorized_keys, i think?) because it\u0027s group- or world-readable, right? i\u0027m not checking anything like that here, so the only permission error i could think of would be one of the keys in ~/.ssh not being user-readable.\n\nbut in any case, logging read errors seems helpful in general, so i\u0027ve updated the code to do that -- thanks for the suggestion. (i\u0027m not logging all errors, because i\u0027m worried about being spammy if the user has passphrase-protected default keys that we can\u0027t get at. most human users are just going to be using the default test key from chromite.)",
